        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Philippians 2:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Because the prophet saw the glory of Christ, the unutterable majesty of the \"Word of God,\" he delivered, as we know, this tremendous burden. Few utterances of the New Testament convey in more startling form the conviction of the apostles touching the pre-existence of the Lord, and the identification of the Divine Personality of the Christ, with the highest conception that the Hebrew prophet entertained of the Almighty One, of the eternal Godhead. John 12:41",
        "children": []
